    <div class="crowd-tip"><strong>Best time:</strong> Monday–Wednesday mornings, particularly in shoulder season (April–May, September–October). Summer weekends (June–August) are the busiest periods across the Bygdøy Peninsula. No timed entry — walk-in year-round. Arrive at opening to board the ships with minimal wait.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-t">FAQ</div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">How much do Fram Museum tickets cost?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Adults €15.50 (180 NOK), Children and Students €6.00 (70 NOK), Seniors (67+) €12.00 (140 NOK), Family (2 adults + 5 children) €34.00 (400 NOK), Groups of 15+ €11.00 per person (130 NOK). Free with Oslo Pass. Purchase at the entrance or online at booking.duell.no — advance booking is not required.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">What are the Fram Museum opening hours?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">October 1–April 30: 10:00–17:00 daily. May 1–September 30: 09:30–18:00 daily. Open every day of the year — no regular closures, no public holiday exceptions.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Can visitors board the Fram and Gjøa ships?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Yes. Both ships are open to walk through as part of standard admission. The polar ship Fram's cabins, lounges, cargo hold and engine room are accessible. The Gjøa — first ship to complete the Northwest Passage — is also open. Access involves steep stairs and tight spaces; a lift and stair lift are available for accessibility.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">How do I get to Fram Museum from central Oslo?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Bus 30 runs every 10 minutes from Jernbanetorget (Central Station), City Hall, and Solli Plass to the Bygdøynes stop, directly in front of the museum (~15 minutes). April–October: ferry from Rådhuskaien 4 to Bygdøynes every 20 minutes — short walk to the entrance. By car: public parking at Bygdøynesveien 37.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Are combined tickets available with other Bygdøy museums?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Yes, purchasable on-site at any of the three museums — not available online. Fram + Kon-Tiki: Adults €27.50 (325 NOK), Seniors €21.50 (250 NOK), Children/Students €10.50 (125 NOK), Family €61.50 (720 NOK). Fram + Norwegian Maritime Museum: Adults €27.50 (325 NOK). All three museums: Adults €41.50 (485 NOK), Seniors €32.50 (380 NOK).</div>
    </div>
  </div>

